If we want to motivate honest provers to use storage rather than work, the following condition 
must hold true for every n ≥ 1, as in [21]: 

 

1) The optimal strategy is storing an ε’-fraction of the honest storage. 

rg min nms* = a s (n (s/n) s)· f · γ ≥ ε′  

2) Rerunning initialization is costlier than storage. 

nw f (0) nmγ   γε + n ≥ ε′ ⇔  ≤ εm′
